metadata.title: Cessna 208 Caravan
aws::graph::propositions: Soloy Pathfinder 21 is a twin-engined stretched fuselage development of the Cessna 208 Caravan.
Soloy Pathfinder 21 was modified by the Soloy Corporation.
Soloy Pathfinder 21 had two PT6D-114A engines mounted side-by-side.
The two PT6D-114A engines on Soloy Pathfinder 21 drove a single propeller.
Soloy Pathfinder 21's fuselage was extended by 70 inches (1.8 m) behind the wing.
Only a single example of Soloy Pathfinder 21 was produced.
The Soloy Pathfinder 21 project was abandoned.
The Soloy Pathfinder 21 project was abandoned because the design was unable to meet certification requirements.
850 Caravan is a modified Cessna 208 Caravan.
850 Caravan has an 850 hp (634 kW) Honeywell TPE331-12JR-701S engine.
The 850 hp engine in 850 Caravan was installed by Aero Twin Inc.
950 Grand Caravan is a modified Cessna 208B Caravan.
950 Grand Caravan has a 1,000 hp (746 kW) Honeywell TPE331-12JR-704AT engine.
The 1,000 hp engine in 950 Grand Caravan was installed by Aero Twin Inc.
Blackhawk Caravan is a conversion of Cessna 208 and 208B Caravan models.
Blackhawk Caravan features an 850 hp (634 kW) PT6A-42A engine.
All aftermarket variants were modified after delivery by Supplemental Type Certificates.

text:
### Aftermarket variants
Production aircraft modified after delivery by Supplemental Type Certificates:

Soloy Pathfinder 21
Single example of a twin-engined stretched fuselage development of the 208 by the Soloy Corporation. Two PT6D-114A engines mounted side-by-side drove a single propeller; and the fuselage was extended by 70 inches (1.8 m) behind the wing. The project was abandoned as the design was unable to meet certification requirements.
850 Caravan
208 with an 850 hp (634 kW) Honeywell TPE331-12JR-701S engine, installed by Aero Twin Inc.
950 Grand Caravan
208B with a 1,000 hp (746 kW) Honeywell TPE331-12JR-704AT engine, installed by Aero Twin Inc.
Blackhawk Caravan
208 and 208B conversion to 850 hp (634 kW) PT6A-42A.
